The paper presents a framework for local clustering in hypergraphs, which involves techniques from graph theory, optimization, and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which covers research on the design and analysis of efficient algorithms and data structures for solving computational problems. The paper also involves applications of machine learning and data mining, which suggest categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses theoretical properties of the proposed algorithm, which could fit into categories such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
